# advertising-creative / react-email

React Email (by Resend) authors responsive HTML emails as React/TypeScript
components, rendering deterministically and headlessly to email-client-safe HTML via
the `@react-email/render` `render()` utility. Deliverables are version-controllable
JSX/TSX source that compile to a single self-contained HTML artifact with no runtime,
network, or browser dependency.

controls do
  advertising-creative.title: { label: "Title / preview", type: "text" }
  advertising-creative.body: { label: "Body copy", type: "textarea" }
  advertising-creative.cta_label: { label: "Button label", type: "text" }
  advertising-creative.cta_href: { label: "Button link", type: "text" }
  advertising-creative.source: { label: "Template source", type: "textarea", file: "src/email.tsx" }
end

## Required reading

- React Email docs & repo — https://github.com/resend/react-email (Resend, MIT).
- `render()` API — `@react-email/render` (async; `{ pretty }`, `{ plainText }`).
- Components — `@react-email/components` (Html, Head, Body, Container, Section, Row,
  Column, Button, Text, Heading, Img, Hr, Link, Preview, Tailwind).
- No official Anthropic/Claude skill exists; agents drive the API/CLI directly.

## Render

```bash
npm install -E @react-email/render @react-email/components react react-dom tsx
# render the template to a single HTML file
npx tsx render.tsx   # await render(<Email/>, { pretty: true }) -> out/email.html
# or CLI static export
npx email export --outDir out --pretty
```

## Failure modes

- `render()` is **async** — forgetting `await` writes `[object Promise]`.
- Browser execution needs `web-streams-polyfill`; Node/Bun/Deno do not.
- Use inline-style / table-safe primitives; raw CSS in `<style>` is stripped by many
  email clients (Gmail/Outlook). Prefer the provided components and Tailwind compile.
- Pass data via props, not string templating, to keep output deterministic/diff-able.
- `email export` scans `./emails` — single-file/props-driven output is easier via the
  tsx entry script.
